19/12/2004
LONDON, United Kingdom -- The Special Co-ordinator of the Stability Pact for South East Europe, Erhard Busek, called on the EU to take a more serious approach toward the Balkans, during a speech delivered at a non-government forum in London on Friday (17 December). He noted that a number of challenges were to be tackled next year, including the future of the state union of Serbia-Montenegro and the status of Kosovo. (Dnevnik - 18/12/04; Beta, B92 - 17/12/04)
